set.seed(54738)

## I. Parameters for simulation
########################################################################################
### Person parameters 
# two dimensions (ability and speed)
# 1000 person per test version (4 different speed values)
group1 <- mvrnorm(250, mu = 0, Sigma = 1)
l <- length(group1)
pers <- data.frame(abil = c(group1, group1, group1, group1), 
                   speed = c(rep(-0.4, l), rep(-0.2, l), rep(0.2, l), rep(0.4, l)))

### Item Parameters
# generate a testform (low discriminating) note: alpha is reversed in the Hierarchical RT model!
# 30 items (2pl for ability, 2pl for speed), but all discriminations equal
# parameters chosen in accordance to van der Linden (2006)
items <- vector("list")
items$lowDis <- data.frame(aDif = mvrnorm(30, 0, 1, empirical = T), 
                    aDis = rep(1, 30),
                    sDif = mvrnorm(30, 4.0, 0.5, empirical = T),
                    sDis = rep(1.8, 30), sPsi = rep(0.5, 30))
                  # sDis = rep(1.3, 30), sPsi = rep(1, 30))

## second testform, identical parameters
items$highDis <- items[[1]]
# shift disc. for speed for second test form
# items$highDis[, 4] <- items[[1]]$sDis + 0.9 ## Error variance shift (van der Linden)
items$highDis$sPsi <- items[[1]]$sPsi + 0.3 ## Error variance shift (Klein Entink/Fox)
# to ensure similar test length, set time intensitiy lower for higher discriminating testform
#items$highDis$sDif <- items[[1]]$sDif # + 0.15


## II. Simulate response data 
########################################################################################
# according to van der Linden RT model (responses and response times)
### responses (for both test forms)
logits <- lapply(items, function(i) irtLogits(theta = pers$abil, alpha = i$aDis, beta = i$aDif))
probits <- lapply(logits, logit2prob)
Ytrue <- lapply(probits, drawResponseDF)

### response times
rtData <- lapply(items, function(i) doRTs(speed = pers$speed, 
                                          sDif = i$sDif, sDis = i$sDis, psi = i$sPsi))
## psi vary between items => KleinEntink/Fox model
## psi vary between items => KleinEntink/Fox model
# insert NAs for not reached items (set time Limit!) and score them as incorrect
Yreal <- Map(function(Y, RT) generateNAs(Ytrue = Y, cumRT = RT$cumResponseTimes, timeLimit = 3100), 
             Y = Ytrue, RT = rtData)

## III. Analysis of response data 
########################################################################################
# missing = incorrect
modList <- Map(function(Y, i) fixedIRT(dat = Y$scoredData, alphas = i$aDif, betas = i$aDis),
               Y = Yreal, i = items)

## set up result data set
plotData <- createPlotData(abil = pers$abil, speed = pers$speed, 
                           lowdisEAP = modList$lowDis$person$EAP, highdisEAP = modList$highDis$person$EAP,
                           lowdisMis = apply(Yreal$lowDis$unscoredData, 1, function(x) sum(is.na(x))),
                           highdisMis = apply(Yreal$highDis$unscoredData, 1, function(x) sum(is.na(x))),
                           lowdisRT = rtData$lowDis$cumResponseTimes[, 30],
                           highdisRT = rtData$highDis$cumResponseTimes[, 30])
